WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:10.920
Billie Elliot, by Melvin Burgess, based on a motion picture screenplay written by Lee

00:10.920 --> 00:12.440
Hall.

00:12.440 --> 00:18.080
Copyright 2005, Universal Studios Licensing, LLLP.

00:18.080 --> 00:24.680
Adapted by Jackie Bloosey.

00:24.680 --> 00:26.240
Chapter 1

00:26.240 --> 00:28.320
Billie, I love to boogie.

00:30.160 --> 00:33.000
I hate my brother.

00:33.000 --> 00:37.520
He's stupid, but he has got some good music.

00:37.520 --> 00:41.280
I listen to his music when he's out at work with my dad.

00:41.280 --> 00:46.080
Well, they're not at work, not now.

00:46.080 --> 00:48.360
They're on strike.

00:48.360 --> 00:52.400
But they still go to the mine every day.

00:52.400 --> 00:55.240
Nan loves the music too.

00:55.240 --> 00:57.800
Tony and Dad leave in the morning.

00:57.800 --> 01:03.960
When the music goes on, I make breakfast for us, and we both dance.

01:03.960 --> 01:06.560
I can hear her in her bedroom.

01:06.560 --> 01:09.920
She tries to dance, but she can't walk very well now.

01:09.920 --> 01:13.400
Well, she is 80.

01:13.400 --> 01:17.120
This morning, I made the eggs and danced to her bedroom.

01:17.120 --> 01:20.920
Hey, Nan, breakfast, I called.

01:20.920 --> 01:27.200
I open the door with my foot and, oh no, not again.

01:27.200 --> 01:29.520
Her bed was empty.

01:29.520 --> 01:33.480
I put the eggs on the kitchen table and ran out of the house.

01:33.480 --> 01:36.080
But where was she?

01:36.080 --> 01:38.000
She does this a lot.

01:38.000 --> 01:40.080
She forgets things.

01:40.080 --> 01:42.840
She forgets her name.

01:42.840 --> 01:45.000
I looked up the street.

01:45.000 --> 01:46.000
Nan?

01:46.000 --> 01:47.480
Nan?

01:47.480 --> 01:49.320
Which way?

01:49.320 --> 01:50.960
Then I had an idea.

01:50.960 --> 01:54.320
I ran to the end of the street and up to some trees.

01:54.320 --> 01:56.600
There she was.

01:56.600 --> 01:58.360
She often goes there.

01:58.360 --> 02:00.320
Why?

02:00.320 --> 02:02.200
Who knows?

02:02.200 --> 02:05.400
Maybe she played there when she was little.

02:05.400 --> 02:06.600
She looked frightened.

02:06.600 --> 02:09.520
Who are you?

02:09.520 --> 02:11.720
She said.

02:11.720 --> 02:15.040
It's me, Nan, Billy.

02:15.040 --> 02:17.160
She didn't look very happy.

02:17.160 --> 02:20.720
Then we both heard something behind us.

02:20.720 --> 02:25.160
On the road, we saw them.

02:25.160 --> 02:33.120
Those of them, the police, their clothes were black and they had battens.

02:33.120 --> 02:34.760
Nan looked at me.

02:34.760 --> 02:37.080
What are they?

02:37.080 --> 02:39.400
She asked.

02:39.400 --> 02:41.880
Police, Nan, it's the police.

02:41.880 --> 02:44.840
Are they here for us?

02:44.840 --> 02:46.480
She asked.

02:46.480 --> 02:50.520
No, Nan, not us, I said.

02:50.520 --> 02:52.480
Is it Jackie?

02:52.480 --> 02:53.480
Is it Tony?

02:53.480 --> 02:54.480
She asked.

02:54.560 --> 02:56.320
I didn't answer.

02:56.320 --> 02:59.040
I didn't want to know the answer.

02:59.040 --> 03:04.760
I took my Nan's arm and we walked slowly home.

03:04.760 --> 03:06.440
I loved to boogie.

03:06.440 --> 03:08.320
Geared above boogie.

03:08.320 --> 03:12.520
I'm trying to play cosmic boogie on the piano and thinking about ma'am.

03:12.520 --> 03:14.360
It was her piano.

03:14.360 --> 03:16.160
Ma'am's dead.

03:16.160 --> 03:18.360
She died two years ago.

03:18.360 --> 03:20.720
I think about her a lot.

03:20.720 --> 03:22.480
I've got a letter from her.

03:22.560 --> 03:25.280
She wrote it before she died.

03:25.280 --> 03:28.680
I'm still here, Billy, she wrote.

03:28.680 --> 03:30.440
But she isn't here.

03:30.440 --> 03:33.000
She's dead.

03:33.000 --> 03:34.840
Ma'am was good at the piano.

03:34.840 --> 03:36.720
She played for all of us.

03:36.720 --> 03:39.760
I'd like piano lessons, but they're too expensive.

03:39.760 --> 03:41.840
We haven't got the money.

03:41.840 --> 03:44.200
My dad's always telling us that.

03:44.200 --> 03:46.520
We haven't got much.

03:46.520 --> 03:49.360
Not now that there's a strike.

03:49.360 --> 03:51.120
Billy, stop that.

03:52.720 --> 03:54.400
It's Dad.

03:54.400 --> 03:57.240
He's going out again with Tony in a minute.

03:57.240 --> 03:59.200
Why do I have to stop?

03:59.200 --> 04:01.320
He's not going to be here.

04:01.320 --> 04:02.200
Why?

04:02.200 --> 04:03.840
Then I say the wrong thing.

04:03.840 --> 04:08.560
If it was ma'am, Dad comes over.

04:08.560 --> 04:11.240
He closes the piano with a bang.

04:11.240 --> 04:14.760
I'm not telling you again.

04:14.760 --> 04:16.960
I go to my room.

04:16.960 --> 04:18.760
Back to Tony's music.

04:22.480 --> 04:30.000
CHAPTER 2

04:30.000 --> 04:31.400
BILLY

04:31.400 --> 04:34.960
BOYS DON'T DO BILLY

04:34.960 --> 04:37.560
BILLY ELLIOT, this isn't a tea party.

04:37.560 --> 04:39.240
It's a boxing lesson.

04:39.240 --> 04:41.360
Heat him.

04:41.360 --> 04:45.600
It's Saturday morning, and I'm at the boxing club at the social.

04:45.600 --> 04:49.960
This morning, I'm against Greavesy, and he's bigger than me.

04:49.960 --> 04:52.440
I have my own ideas about boxing.

04:52.440 --> 04:54.680
It's all about your feet.

04:54.680 --> 04:57.160
So I run and turn and jump.

04:57.160 --> 04:59.040
I move quickly.

04:59.040 --> 05:01.840
Greavesy just stands there.

05:01.840 --> 05:04.680
George, the teacher, isn't happy.

05:04.680 --> 05:05.760
Heat him.

05:05.760 --> 05:07.880
Don't dance around.

05:07.880 --> 05:08.880
Bang.

05:08.880 --> 05:10.560
I'm on the floor.

05:10.560 --> 05:13.760
Greaves is standing over me and he's smiling.

05:13.760 --> 05:15.400
I can hear George.

05:15.400 --> 05:17.400
Billy Elliot, get up.

05:17.400 --> 05:19.560
You're going to do it right.

05:19.560 --> 05:22.400
You're not going home yet.

05:22.400 --> 05:23.920
I get up.

05:23.920 --> 05:26.360
George pulls me to the punch bag.

05:26.360 --> 05:28.080
Hit it.

05:28.080 --> 05:30.200
You're poor father.

05:30.200 --> 05:34.240
He pays for boxing lessons, and this happens.

05:34.240 --> 05:35.600
And on.

05:35.600 --> 05:37.040
And on.

05:37.040 --> 05:38.960
And on.

05:38.960 --> 05:41.280
I'm angry now.

05:41.280 --> 05:43.240
I hit the punch bag.

05:43.240 --> 05:47.320
I hate the punch bag.

05:47.320 --> 05:48.440
Arms up.

05:48.440 --> 05:49.200
And one.

05:49.200 --> 05:49.800
And two.

05:49.800 --> 05:50.400
And three.

05:50.400 --> 05:51.360
And four.

05:51.360 --> 05:54.280
Feel the music.

05:54.280 --> 05:58.400
On the other side of the room, there's a ballet class.

05:58.400 --> 06:01.000
Someone's playing the piano.

06:01.000 --> 06:04.760
One and two and three and four.

06:04.760 --> 06:08.640
As the music plays, I hit the punch bag.

06:08.640 --> 06:10.000
One and two.

06:10.000 --> 06:11.640
And bang and hit.

06:11.640 --> 06:13.200
And three and four.

06:13.200 --> 06:15.120
And hit and bang.

06:15.120 --> 06:17.960
That's better, George says.

06:17.960 --> 06:20.680
Stay here and get it right.

06:20.680 --> 06:22.680
See you next week.

06:22.680 --> 06:24.560
And he goes out.

06:24.560 --> 06:27.720
All the other boys go too.

06:27.720 --> 06:28.920
Right girls.

06:28.920 --> 06:30.560
And one and two.

06:30.560 --> 06:32.320
Debbie, don't look at me.

06:32.320 --> 06:34.000
Look in front of you.

06:34.000 --> 06:36.480
And three and four.

06:36.480 --> 06:38.280
I go and watch.

06:38.280 --> 06:39.960
It's clever.

06:39.960 --> 06:42.160
They all dance together.

06:42.160 --> 06:45.920
Left and two and down and two and turn and two.

06:45.920 --> 06:47.240
I try it.

06:47.240 --> 06:48.520
I stretch out my leg.

06:48.600 --> 06:51.600
Yeah, easy.

06:51.600 --> 06:53.480
Why don't you try?

06:53.480 --> 06:54.760
It's Debbie.

06:54.760 --> 06:56.520
She goes to my school.

06:56.520 --> 06:58.280
Nah, I say.

06:58.280 --> 07:00.480
Boys don't do ballet.

07:00.480 --> 07:02.440
Legs up.

07:02.440 --> 07:04.680
They all stretch their legs.

07:04.680 --> 07:07.280
Mrs. Wilkinson, she's the teacher,

07:07.280 --> 07:11.080
walks around and looks closely at each leg.

07:11.080 --> 07:13.120
I try it.

07:13.120 --> 07:14.920
Debbie laughs at me.

07:14.920 --> 07:17.200
Your legs moving.

07:17.200 --> 07:18.320
I look down.

07:18.320 --> 07:20.280
She's right.

07:20.280 --> 07:23.720
I'm wearing boxing shoes, I tell her.

07:23.720 --> 07:27.120
Mrs. Wilkinson takes a cigarette from her pocket.

07:27.120 --> 07:29.120
She smokes a lot.

07:29.120 --> 07:30.600
OK girls.

07:30.600 --> 07:34.800
And one and two and three and four.

07:34.800 --> 07:36.840
I want to do it too.

07:36.840 --> 07:39.120
I try, but it's difficult.

07:39.120 --> 07:41.280
I start to listen to the music.

07:41.280 --> 07:43.240
It's easier then.

07:43.240 --> 07:44.600
Shoes off.

07:44.600 --> 07:46.360
Mrs. in front of me.

07:46.360 --> 07:48.760
But not me, Miss, I start to say.

07:48.760 --> 07:51.400
But she's already walking down the room.

07:51.400 --> 07:54.280
I take off my shoes and then she's back again.

07:54.280 --> 07:56.280
With ballet shoes.

07:56.280 --> 07:58.240
Here you are, she says.

07:58.240 --> 08:00.880
You can't dance in boxing shoes.

08:00.880 --> 08:07.200
I don't know, but then I think, why not?

08:07.200 --> 08:08.680
So I do it.

08:08.680 --> 08:11.520
I do ballet for the first time.

08:11.520 --> 08:14.960
It isn't easy, but Miss is a good teacher.

08:14.960 --> 08:18.600
We're all standing on one leg with the other leg behind.

08:18.600 --> 08:20.800
Miss comes over.

08:20.800 --> 08:24.640
I like the leg, she says, and then walks off.

08:24.640 --> 08:28.240
She doesn't say much, but I'm happy.

08:28.240 --> 08:31.280
I'm walking home later and Miss drives by.

08:31.280 --> 08:33.960
She sees me and stops the car.

08:33.960 --> 08:36.440
Debbie's sitting in the back.

08:36.440 --> 08:37.560
Oh, I think.

08:37.560 --> 08:39.960
Debbie's her daughter.

08:39.960 --> 08:42.080
Miss is still smoking.

08:42.080 --> 08:44.040
She looks at me.

08:44.040 --> 08:46.440
It's 50p a lesson, you know.

08:46.440 --> 08:48.960
Bring me the money next week.

08:48.960 --> 08:50.040
I can't.

08:50.040 --> 08:51.480
I'm going to boxing.

08:51.480 --> 08:55.000
Your terrible at boxing says Debbie and laughs.

08:55.000 --> 08:56.880
Be quiet.

08:56.880 --> 09:00.320
Miss looks round at Debbie and then back at me.

09:00.320 --> 09:02.640
Didn't you enjoy it today?

09:02.640 --> 09:04.680
I don't say anything.

09:04.680 --> 09:08.400
It's your life, she says, and off they go.

09:08.400 --> 09:10.360
Miss was right.

09:10.360 --> 09:12.240
I enjoyed it.

09:12.240 --> 09:14.920
But the music was a bit boring.

09:14.920 --> 09:17.400
I think about Fred Astaire.

09:17.400 --> 09:19.200
My man loves him.

09:19.200 --> 09:20.800
He can dance.

09:20.800 --> 09:23.160
I want to dance like him.

09:23.160 --> 09:25.520
I run and jump down the road.

09:25.520 --> 09:27.800
Fred Astaire's music is playing in my head,

09:27.800 --> 09:28.920
and I feel great.

09:28.920 --> 09:44.360
Chapter 3, Billy, do the spin.

09:44.360 --> 09:47.440
I think about ballet all the time.

09:47.440 --> 09:50.320
One and two and up and down.

09:50.320 --> 09:54.360
Miss's words and the music are always in my head.

09:54.360 --> 09:56.040
But there's a problem.

09:56.040 --> 09:58.720
I feel stupid.

09:58.720 --> 10:00.600
And then there's my dad.

10:00.600 --> 10:04.400
And Tony, miners don't do ballet.

10:04.400 --> 10:07.560
Miners sons don't do ballet.

10:07.560 --> 10:11.880
Miners don't do much when they're on strike.

10:11.880 --> 10:14.080
The strike is going to end soon.

10:14.080 --> 10:16.120
I heard it on the TV.

10:16.120 --> 10:18.400
The cold weather's coming.

10:18.400 --> 10:22.880
The strikers and their families are going to be cold and hungry.

10:22.880 --> 10:25.200
They're going to need money.

10:25.200 --> 10:29.600
The strike is going to be over by Christmas.

10:29.600 --> 10:32.680
People know about the ballet at school, but I don't care.

10:32.680 --> 10:34.680
Some of the boys laugh at me.

10:34.680 --> 10:38.440
Hey, Billy, where are you pink ballet shoes today?

10:38.440 --> 10:40.520
What do they know?

10:40.520 --> 10:43.360
Debbie Wilkinson's always talking to me, too.

10:43.360 --> 10:47.320
She and her mama posh, not like my family.

10:47.320 --> 10:50.680
She walked home with me from school the other day.

10:50.680 --> 10:54.160
Lots of boys do ballet, you know, she said.

10:54.160 --> 10:56.280
Don't be stupid, who?

10:56.280 --> 10:58.320
Who do we know?

10:58.320 --> 11:01.200
No one here, but lots of men do it.

11:01.200 --> 11:03.520
Are you coming next week?

11:03.520 --> 11:04.920
She looked at me.

11:04.920 --> 11:06.320
I'm going to boxing.

11:06.320 --> 11:09.800
My dad says, I said, I was a bit angry.

11:09.800 --> 11:11.120
OK.

11:11.120 --> 11:12.840
She walked off.

11:12.840 --> 11:16.120
She lives in the nice part of town, in a posh house

11:16.120 --> 11:17.880
with a posh garden.

11:17.880 --> 11:21.680
Her and her mom don't know anything about our life.

11:21.680 --> 11:24.560
Then the music comes back in my head.

11:24.560 --> 11:28.280
I start to dance, and I forget about my life, too.

11:30.920 --> 11:32.960
I've got this friend, Michael.

11:32.960 --> 11:36.800
He hates football, not like me.

11:36.800 --> 11:40.120
We're different, but we're best friends.

11:40.120 --> 11:42.240
I can talk to him about things.

11:42.240 --> 11:44.360
I told him about the ballet.

11:44.360 --> 11:46.000
I did some of the moves.

11:46.000 --> 11:47.600
He thinks it's cool.

11:47.600 --> 11:49.880
Leg out, arm out, one, two, I said.

11:49.880 --> 11:51.400
Eyes to the front.

11:51.400 --> 11:52.600
Michael laughed.

11:52.600 --> 11:54.680
Oh, when's the next lesson?

11:54.680 --> 11:56.440
I'm not going, I said.

11:56.440 --> 11:57.920
Bal is for girls.

11:57.920 --> 11:59.560
I feel stupid.

11:59.560 --> 12:02.120
You are stupid, Michael laughed.

12:02.120 --> 12:04.240
Anyway, it's not just for girls.

12:04.240 --> 12:05.280
It's different for men.

12:05.280 --> 12:07.560
Men are stronger.

12:07.560 --> 12:09.280
He was right.

12:09.280 --> 12:12.240
I can jump higher than the girls in the ballet class,

12:12.240 --> 12:15.120
and I'm better than most of them.

12:15.120 --> 12:17.080
So I went again.

12:17.080 --> 12:20.200
On Saturday, I took my 50p from the kitchen table,

12:20.200 --> 12:22.600
and I went to the social.

12:22.600 --> 12:25.360
This week, the class was in a different room.

12:25.360 --> 12:28.840
That was good because I didn't want to see George.

12:28.840 --> 12:31.360
At the start, it was boring.

12:31.360 --> 12:34.000
I didn't know the moves, so I stopped.

12:34.000 --> 12:36.000
Miss came over.

12:36.000 --> 12:37.720
What are you doing?

12:37.720 --> 12:40.040
I don't know the moves, Miss, I said.

12:40.040 --> 12:41.400
Follow the girls.

12:41.400 --> 12:43.280
Go to the back and watch them.

12:43.280 --> 12:46.800
And one, two, three.

12:46.800 --> 12:50.480
That was OK, but it was still a bit boring.

12:50.480 --> 12:52.400
Then Miss showed us the spin.

12:52.400 --> 12:56.240
You spin around and around very fast, and then you stop.

12:56.240 --> 12:58.480
You must stay in the same place.

12:58.480 --> 13:00.680
It looks great, but it's very difficult.

13:00.680 --> 13:02.360
You fall on the floor a lot.

13:02.360 --> 13:04.280
We all tried it.

13:04.280 --> 13:06.400
Do it at home, Miss said.

13:06.400 --> 13:08.040
Try again and again.

13:08.040 --> 13:10.480
You can do it.

13:10.480 --> 13:13.640
At the end of the class, Miss came over to me.

13:13.640 --> 13:16.600
So are you coming next week?

13:16.600 --> 13:18.640
I don't know, Miss.

13:18.640 --> 13:20.840
She looks at my ballet shoes.

13:20.840 --> 13:23.640
Give me those, then.

13:23.640 --> 13:25.040
I didn't want to.

13:25.040 --> 13:28.080
I wanted to learn the spin and do it at boxing.

13:28.080 --> 13:31.000
I wanted to see George's face.

13:31.000 --> 13:35.040
No, it's OK, I said, and gave him a 50p.

13:35.040 --> 13:37.400
She took it and went off.

13:37.400 --> 13:40.040
She didn't say anything.

13:40.040 --> 13:43.480
At home, Nan was in the kitchen.

13:43.480 --> 13:45.160
Ballet shoes.

13:45.160 --> 13:46.440
How lovely.

13:46.440 --> 13:51.280
She said, don't tell Dad, I said, and ran into my room.

13:51.280 --> 13:54.440
Luckily, Dad and Tony were out.

13:54.440 --> 13:58.640
Dad is not going to understand about ballet shoes.

13:58.640 --> 14:02.680
Dad isn't going to understand about any of this.

14:02.680 --> 14:05.880
I put the ballet shoes under my bed with my boxing things.

14:05.880 --> 14:08.960
Anyway, I'm going to go to boxing soon.

14:08.960 --> 14:11.960
I'm going to go when I can do the spin.

14:12.080 --> 14:21.000
MUSIC

14:21.000 --> 14:26.480
Chapter 4, Jackie, my son Billy.

14:26.480 --> 14:30.320
There's something funny about Billy at the moment.

14:30.320 --> 14:32.800
He's a bit different from the other boys.

14:32.800 --> 14:34.200
I know that.

14:34.200 --> 14:37.640
But now, it's this spinning.

14:37.640 --> 14:39.480
He does it everywhere.

14:39.480 --> 14:43.120
He puts out his arms and spins around and around.

14:43.120 --> 14:46.920
He looks a bit stupid, like a girl.

14:46.920 --> 14:50.240
He doesn't care, not Billy.

14:50.240 --> 14:53.040
It's a boxing move, he tells me.

14:53.040 --> 14:54.960
Boxing.

14:54.960 --> 14:58.200
Sometimes, I can't believe Billy is my son.

14:58.200 --> 15:01.640
Then, there's the strike.

15:01.640 --> 15:04.200
We started four months ago.

15:04.200 --> 15:06.280
We're so poor now.

15:06.280 --> 15:09.200
We haven't got money for anything.

15:09.200 --> 15:11.240
What's going to happen?

15:11.240 --> 15:12.800
We don't know.

15:12.800 --> 15:15.760
Maybe they're going to close the mines.

15:15.760 --> 15:18.720
Maybe they decided a long time ago.

15:18.720 --> 15:21.640
So why are we doing this?

15:21.640 --> 15:22.920
Tone is angry.

15:22.920 --> 15:27.080
I see it in his eyes every day at the mine.

15:27.080 --> 15:30.840
What's it going to do if there's no mine?

15:30.840 --> 15:33.120
Some men choose to work.

15:33.120 --> 15:35.600
We call them scabs.

15:35.600 --> 15:38.440
The strikers stand together at the mine.

15:38.520 --> 15:40.880
The scabs go through in buses.

15:40.880 --> 15:43.200
There are police everywhere.

15:43.200 --> 15:44.840
We shout at the buses.

15:44.840 --> 15:46.720
We bang on the windows.

15:46.720 --> 15:48.720
The scabs look frightened.

15:48.720 --> 15:51.040
I'm not surprised.

15:51.040 --> 15:53.640
This morning, I was next to George.

15:53.640 --> 15:55.000
It was cold.

15:55.000 --> 15:57.560
We waited for the scab buses.

15:57.560 --> 15:59.720
Listen, Jackie, he said.

15:59.720 --> 16:01.160
Forget the money.

16:01.160 --> 16:03.080
The 50P for the boxing.

16:03.080 --> 16:05.440
I don't do it for the money.

16:05.440 --> 16:07.120
What?

16:07.120 --> 16:09.560
I didn't understand.

16:09.560 --> 16:11.280
It's Billy.

16:11.280 --> 16:13.400
He doesn't come to boxing now.

16:13.400 --> 16:15.960
Is it because of the money?

16:15.960 --> 16:18.160
I started to think.

16:18.160 --> 16:21.600
Where did Billy go every Saturday morning?

16:21.600 --> 16:24.000
Then a bus came in and everyone started a shout.

16:24.000 --> 16:27.720
Scab, scab, scab.

16:27.720 --> 16:29.840
I shouted with the other men.

16:29.840 --> 16:32.720
But I thought about other things.

16:32.720 --> 16:34.760
Tomorrow was Saturday.

16:34.760 --> 16:37.200
Billy's boxing day.

16:37.200 --> 16:38.240
I had an idea.

16:47.840 --> 16:49.360
Chapter 5.

16:49.360 --> 16:52.360
Billy, just you and me.

16:52.360 --> 16:54.080
I can spin now.

16:54.080 --> 16:56.800
I can do everything, all the moves.

16:56.800 --> 16:59.480
Miss teaches me for a lot of the lesson.

16:59.480 --> 17:02.520
The girls aren't happy about it.

17:02.520 --> 17:04.240
Miss, what about us?

17:04.240 --> 17:05.880
They say.

17:05.880 --> 17:07.120
She doesn't listen.

17:07.120 --> 17:09.160
I'm busy.

17:09.160 --> 17:11.040
Then it happened.

17:11.040 --> 17:14.520
Michael often said to me, what about your dad?

17:14.520 --> 17:16.400
What are you going to do?

17:16.400 --> 17:18.920
Yeah, it happened.

17:18.920 --> 17:21.320
I was in the center of the class.

17:21.320 --> 17:23.280
Miss was next to me.

17:23.280 --> 17:25.800
And stretch your leg, Billy.

17:25.800 --> 17:27.440
I looked up.

17:27.440 --> 17:29.760
And there he was by the door.

17:29.760 --> 17:32.120
His face was red.

17:32.120 --> 17:34.000
Miss all in two.

17:34.000 --> 17:36.440
The music stopped.

17:36.440 --> 17:40.120
You out now, he shouted.

17:40.120 --> 17:43.280
Miss wanted to say something, but I stopped her.

17:43.280 --> 17:45.400
I had enough problems.

17:45.400 --> 17:49.760
I followed Dad out of the social.

17:49.760 --> 17:51.280
Billy?

17:51.280 --> 17:52.920
We were in the kitchen.

17:52.920 --> 17:55.440
Dad didn't speak to me when we left the social.

17:55.440 --> 17:57.440
Maybe he was too angry.

17:57.440 --> 17:59.160
I don't know.

17:59.160 --> 18:00.680
What's wrong with Billy?

18:00.680 --> 18:03.840
I said, lots of people do it.

18:03.840 --> 18:06.400
Dad's face was red again.

18:06.400 --> 18:09.800
Lots of girls do ballet, Billy, not boys.

18:09.800 --> 18:12.960
Boys do football or boxing.

18:12.960 --> 18:14.880
It was true in a way.

18:14.880 --> 18:16.640
Ballet isn't boxing.

18:16.640 --> 18:18.840
You don't hit anyone.

18:18.840 --> 18:20.800
It's not mining.

18:20.800 --> 18:23.520
So my dad can't understand it.

18:23.520 --> 18:26.080
So it's not boxing or mining.

18:26.080 --> 18:27.600
Well, so what?

18:27.600 --> 18:29.320
I'm not the same as my dad.

18:29.320 --> 18:31.560
I can be different.

18:31.560 --> 18:33.560
I like dancing, Dad.

18:33.560 --> 18:34.680
That's all it is.

18:34.680 --> 18:35.680
Dancing.

18:35.680 --> 18:37.720
Why is that so bad?

18:37.720 --> 18:39.760
Listen, forget about dancing.

18:39.760 --> 18:40.880
You're not doing it.

18:40.880 --> 18:42.840
Understand?

18:42.840 --> 18:45.320
I jumped up and shouted in his face.

18:45.320 --> 18:46.840
I hate you.

18:46.840 --> 18:48.320
I run out of the house.

18:48.320 --> 18:49.480
I ran and ran.

18:49.480 --> 18:51.600
I hated my dad.

18:51.600 --> 18:54.360
I loved dancing, and I was good at it.

18:54.360 --> 18:55.920
I knew that.

18:55.920 --> 18:58.120
Miss knew it too.

18:58.120 --> 18:59.720
Suddenly, I wanted to see her.

18:59.720 --> 19:04.840
I was in Mrs. House.

19:04.840 --> 19:06.040
It was funny.

19:06.040 --> 19:09.880
Me, Debbie, Miss, and her husband.

19:09.880 --> 19:11.680
He was funny too.

19:11.680 --> 19:14.120
It was always in the pub, Debbie said.

19:14.120 --> 19:16.120
He always had a beer in his hand.

19:16.120 --> 19:19.080
Oh, it's little Jean Kelly.

19:19.080 --> 19:20.320
He said when he saw me.

19:20.320 --> 19:23.080
Be quiet, Tom, Miss said.

19:23.080 --> 19:25.560
You're not in the pub now?

19:25.560 --> 19:27.400
I had dinner with them.

19:27.480 --> 19:30.840
Later, Miss took me home in her car.

19:30.840 --> 19:34.440
She stopped near my house and looked at me.

19:34.440 --> 19:38.800
Billy, I'm thinking about the Royal Ballet School.

19:38.800 --> 19:41.240
Aren't you a bit old, Miss, I said?

19:41.240 --> 19:43.160
Not me, you.

19:43.160 --> 19:47.480
There's an audition a new castle in two weeks.

19:47.480 --> 19:49.040
Ballet School.

19:49.040 --> 19:50.600
Me.

19:50.600 --> 19:52.520
Ballet.

19:52.520 --> 19:54.240
All day.

19:54.240 --> 19:57.200
Every day.

19:57.200 --> 20:01.400
Can you do Ballet as a job, then, Miss, I asked her?

20:01.400 --> 20:04.600
Yes, if you're good enough.

20:04.600 --> 20:06.920
But I don't know anything.

20:06.920 --> 20:10.040
Look, she took a cigarette from her bag.

20:10.040 --> 20:11.320
They teach you.

20:11.320 --> 20:15.080
It's a school, and she waited a minute.

20:15.080 --> 20:18.000
I think you're good enough.

20:18.000 --> 20:19.920
Wow.

20:19.920 --> 20:22.680
She didn't usually say anything nice.

20:22.680 --> 20:25.000
What about my dad?

20:25.080 --> 20:27.440
I can speak to him if you want.

20:27.440 --> 20:29.880
No, please, Miss.

20:29.880 --> 20:32.720
I knew my dad.

20:32.720 --> 20:35.160
I can give you more lessons, she said.

20:35.160 --> 20:36.640
Just you and me.

20:36.640 --> 20:38.040
Don't think about the money.

20:38.040 --> 20:40.480
I'm not doing it for the money.

20:40.480 --> 20:41.920
I thought about it.

20:41.920 --> 20:45.400
My dad didn't know about it, and that was wrong.

20:45.400 --> 20:48.400
But I wanted to be a dancer.

20:48.400 --> 20:50.200
I smiled at Miss.

20:50.200 --> 20:51.840
OK, then.

20:51.840 --> 20:53.600
She smiled, too.

20:53.600 --> 20:56.520
She didn't usually smile.

20:56.520 --> 20:59.680
6 o'clock on Monday at the social, she said.

20:59.680 --> 21:00.880
OK.

21:00.880 --> 21:02.600
I opened the car door.

21:02.600 --> 21:05.920
Oh, and Billy, bring something with you.

21:05.920 --> 21:08.080
Something that's important to you.

21:08.080 --> 21:10.520
We must think of an idea for the audition dance.

21:10.520 --> 21:25.800
Chapter 6, Billy, Mam's Dance.

21:25.800 --> 21:27.960
There wasn't much time.

21:27.960 --> 21:30.720
The audition was in two weeks.

21:30.720 --> 21:32.680
I met Miss almost every night.

21:32.680 --> 21:37.200
I'm going to Michael's house, I told Dad.

21:37.200 --> 21:40.400
The first evening, I had some things with me.

21:40.400 --> 21:45.640
My football, some T-Rex music, I liked to boogie.

21:45.640 --> 21:48.920
It was Tony's, I didn't ask him.

21:48.920 --> 21:52.440
Then there was the letter from my mom.

21:52.440 --> 21:54.640
Miss started to read the letter.

21:54.640 --> 21:57.240
Dear Billy, she stopped.

21:57.240 --> 21:59.600
Can I read this, Billy?

21:59.600 --> 22:01.880
Yeah, I said.

22:01.880 --> 22:04.400
I'm still here, Billy.

22:04.400 --> 22:06.080
You can't see me.

22:06.080 --> 22:07.080
But I am.

22:07.080 --> 22:09.080
I'm always with you.

22:09.080 --> 22:10.960
Don't forget that.

22:10.960 --> 22:12.480
And I love you.

22:12.480 --> 22:17.320
Be true to Billy Elliot, all your life.

22:17.320 --> 22:19.320
Miss looked away and didn't say anything.

22:19.320 --> 22:23.400
You OK, Miss, I asked.

22:23.400 --> 22:26.920
She's going to cry, I thought.

22:26.920 --> 22:29.440
She was a very special person, Billy.

22:29.440 --> 22:35.440
She said, nah, she was just my mom, I said.

22:35.440 --> 22:39.040
What did your mom like doing, chest me?

22:39.040 --> 22:41.320
She liked music, I said.

22:41.320 --> 22:43.720
And then we listened to the T-Rex music.

22:43.720 --> 22:45.480
I liked to boogie.

22:45.480 --> 22:47.560
Gee her bug boogie.

22:47.560 --> 22:49.320
I liked to boogie.

22:49.320 --> 22:52.160
On a Saturday night.

22:52.160 --> 22:55.240
It's happy music, Miss said.

22:55.240 --> 22:57.200
Dance music.

22:57.200 --> 22:59.480
And your mom liked this.

22:59.480 --> 23:00.920
I?

23:00.920 --> 23:02.960
Then this is our dance, Billy.

23:02.960 --> 23:04.720
Let's go.

23:04.720 --> 23:07.520
We danced and jumped and ran around.

23:07.520 --> 23:09.960
We thought of lots of new moves.

23:09.960 --> 23:13.040
Now, think about your mom, Miss said.

23:13.040 --> 23:14.160
She's watching you.

23:14.160 --> 23:17.120
She's smiling and laughing.

23:17.120 --> 23:18.800
And it worked.

23:18.800 --> 23:21.720
I thought about mom, and I did a great spin.

23:21.720 --> 23:22.880
I was on top of the world.

23:25.880 --> 23:28.920
At home, things were very different.

23:28.920 --> 23:31.560
No one was on top of the world.

23:31.560 --> 23:35.080
There were police all over the town.

23:35.080 --> 23:37.240
They frightened me.

23:37.240 --> 23:39.640
Tony was never frightened.

23:39.640 --> 23:41.920
He shouted a lot at Dad.

23:41.920 --> 23:43.680
What's wrong with you?

23:43.680 --> 23:46.720
This strike is our only hope.

23:46.720 --> 23:48.800
Dad didn't answer.

23:48.800 --> 23:52.000
He just sat there and said nothing.

23:52.000 --> 23:55.160
I was sorry for him.

23:55.160 --> 24:00.640
Tonight, I'm in bed, and I hear something in the kitchen.

24:00.640 --> 24:02.920
It's Dad and Tony.

24:02.920 --> 24:04.760
I sit up and listen.

24:04.800 --> 24:07.560
Tony sounds very angry.

24:07.560 --> 24:11.480
I'm not going to sit at home and do nothing, he shouts.

24:11.480 --> 24:14.400
You think it's the end, but for me, it's the start.

24:14.400 --> 24:16.640
Now move.

24:16.640 --> 24:18.680
I run into the kitchen.

24:18.680 --> 24:21.760
Tony has a button, a police button.

24:21.760 --> 24:23.160
Where did he get that?

24:23.160 --> 24:25.520
What's he going to do with it?

24:25.520 --> 24:27.560
This time, Dad shouts back.

24:27.560 --> 24:29.160
You're not going.

24:29.160 --> 24:31.280
And you're not going to use that.

24:31.280 --> 24:32.840
He's looking at the button.

24:32.840 --> 24:34.640
Forget about the police.

24:34.640 --> 24:35.880
They're doing a job.

24:35.880 --> 24:38.000
That's all.

24:38.000 --> 24:40.720
Try and stop me then, says Tony.

24:40.720 --> 24:42.120
You can't do anything.

24:42.120 --> 24:43.640
You're nothing.

24:43.640 --> 24:47.560
Without ma'am, you're nothing.

24:47.560 --> 24:49.320
They're by the back door.

24:49.320 --> 24:51.920
Dad's face is white.

24:51.920 --> 24:54.080
Suddenly, he hits Tony.

24:54.080 --> 24:56.000
Crack.

24:56.000 --> 24:58.600
Tony falls to the floor.

24:58.600 --> 24:59.840
Stop it.

24:59.840 --> 25:00.680
Stop it.

25:00.680 --> 25:02.760
I shout.

25:02.760 --> 25:05.240
Tony gets up slowly.

25:05.240 --> 25:07.360
He doesn't say a word.

25:07.360 --> 25:09.480
He doesn't look at Dad.

25:09.480 --> 25:12.480
He just runs out of the door.

25:12.480 --> 25:15.240
The button is under his arm.

25:15.240 --> 25:16.920
Dad doesn't stop him this time.

25:26.680 --> 25:31.840
Chapter 7, Billy Black Friday.

25:31.840 --> 25:34.000
Billy, you're not trying.

25:34.000 --> 25:35.800
Arm up.

25:35.800 --> 25:37.280
What?

25:37.280 --> 25:38.960
I'm at the social with miss.

25:38.960 --> 25:42.360
But I can only think about last night and my dad and Tony.

25:42.360 --> 25:44.320
Eyes to the front.

25:44.320 --> 25:45.120
Bang.

25:45.120 --> 25:46.840
Dad hits Tony.

25:46.840 --> 25:48.600
Do it again, Billy.

25:48.600 --> 25:49.240
Bang.

25:49.240 --> 25:50.880
Tony's on the floor.

25:50.880 --> 25:53.480
Billy, that's not good enough.

25:53.480 --> 25:54.880
I can't.

25:54.880 --> 25:56.760
Suddenly, I hate her.

25:56.760 --> 25:59.960
She's standing right next to me and smoking in my face.

25:59.960 --> 26:01.800
Do it again, she says.

26:01.800 --> 26:03.400
No.

26:03.400 --> 26:04.680
What?

26:04.680 --> 26:06.720
She can't believe it.

26:06.720 --> 26:09.680
Suddenly, I am angry about everything.

26:09.680 --> 26:14.320
Last night, the audition, everything's going wrong.

26:14.320 --> 26:16.240
Tony was right about one thing.

26:16.240 --> 26:18.840
Without ma'am, we're all nothing.

26:18.840 --> 26:21.680
And she's never coming back.

26:21.680 --> 26:23.160
I run out of the room.

26:23.160 --> 26:24.880
Miss follows me.

26:24.880 --> 26:27.320
Billy, I'm sorry, she says.

26:27.320 --> 26:29.040
I want to help you.

26:29.040 --> 26:30.240
No, you don't.

26:30.320 --> 26:31.560
The audition's for you.

26:31.560 --> 26:32.760
Not for me.

26:32.760 --> 26:35.880
That's not true, she says.

26:35.880 --> 26:37.520
I can't stop now.

26:37.520 --> 26:38.600
What have you got?

26:38.600 --> 26:39.640
Nothing.

26:39.640 --> 26:40.880
No dance school.

26:40.880 --> 26:41.720
What are you?

26:41.720 --> 26:42.800
You're nothing.

26:42.800 --> 26:44.960
Don't speak to me like that.

26:44.960 --> 26:47.200
Then she hits me across the face.

26:47.200 --> 26:49.320
She looks very surprised.

26:49.320 --> 26:51.360
I'm surprised, too.

26:51.360 --> 26:52.560
I want to run.

26:52.560 --> 26:55.400
But I can't leave.

26:55.400 --> 26:57.640
I must dance.

26:57.640 --> 26:59.880
And because I can't leave, I start

26:59.880 --> 27:01.840
to cry.

27:01.840 --> 27:04.000
She puts out her arms.

27:04.000 --> 27:06.160
I'm sorry, Billy.

27:06.160 --> 27:09.880
And I cry in her arms for about five minutes.

27:09.880 --> 27:12.640
I can't stop.

27:12.640 --> 27:14.720
Right, she says.

27:14.720 --> 27:16.640
Is that enough?

27:16.640 --> 27:18.720
Yes, I say.

27:18.720 --> 27:20.680
Sorry, Miss.

27:20.680 --> 27:24.040
Right, then, she says, let's start again.

27:25.040 --> 27:29.040
There was something different about that Friday.

27:29.040 --> 27:32.040
Black Friday, Dad called it.

27:32.040 --> 27:35.040
The audition was the next morning.

27:35.040 --> 27:38.040
I walked home after my last lesson with Miss.

27:38.040 --> 27:40.040
I was happy.

27:40.040 --> 27:43.040
I did my audition dance in my head.

27:43.040 --> 27:46.040
Then I turned into our road.

27:46.040 --> 27:48.040
And saw them all.

27:48.040 --> 27:51.040
There were police everywhere.

27:51.040 --> 27:53.040
Mrs. Watts lives near us.

27:53.040 --> 27:55.040
She saw me and pulled me into her house.

27:55.040 --> 27:57.040
Get in, Billy.

27:57.040 --> 27:59.040
What's happening?

27:59.040 --> 28:00.040
It's your Tony.

28:00.040 --> 28:01.040
He's in trouble.

28:01.040 --> 28:03.040
The police wants him.

28:03.040 --> 28:04.040
Tony?

28:04.040 --> 28:07.040
I didn't understand.

28:07.040 --> 28:09.040
Where did he go at night?

28:09.040 --> 28:11.040
What did he do?

28:11.040 --> 28:16.040
My dad and Tony, especially Tony, hate the police.

28:16.040 --> 28:20.040
Now, I understand.

28:20.040 --> 28:22.040
I saw one man.

28:22.040 --> 28:25.040
He was in front of one of the police.

28:25.040 --> 28:28.040
The policeman hit him with his baton.

28:28.040 --> 28:30.040
He didn't stop.

28:30.040 --> 28:33.040
He hit him again and again.

28:33.040 --> 28:35.040
Then I saw our Tony.

28:35.040 --> 28:39.040
He ran up the road with the police all around him.

28:39.040 --> 28:41.040
They were faster than him.

28:41.040 --> 28:42.040
I ran to the door.

28:42.040 --> 28:44.040
Tony, in here.

28:44.040 --> 28:46.040
He didn't hear me.

28:46.040 --> 28:47.040
It was too loud.

28:47.040 --> 28:48.040
Everyone shouted.

28:48.040 --> 28:51.040
Batons banged on doors.

28:51.040 --> 28:55.040
After that, I saw about 20 police, all together.

28:55.040 --> 28:58.040
And our Tony was under them.

29:07.040 --> 29:10.040
Chapter 8, Tony.

29:10.040 --> 29:12.040
Happy Christmas.

29:12.040 --> 29:15.040
I stared in the police station that night.

29:15.040 --> 29:17.040
There was no bed.

29:17.040 --> 29:19.040
Where do I sleep?

29:19.040 --> 29:20.040
I asked.

29:20.040 --> 29:22.040
They laughed.

29:22.040 --> 29:24.040
I was black and blue.

29:24.040 --> 29:27.040
I hate the police.

29:27.040 --> 29:30.040
Next morning, I sat in the courtroom.

29:30.040 --> 29:33.040
There was a big policeman next to me.

29:33.040 --> 29:36.040
I saw Dad and our Billy.

29:36.040 --> 29:39.040
Dad was angry, but he didn't say anything.

29:39.040 --> 29:42.040
It was over very quickly.

29:42.040 --> 29:46.040
Pay the court 100 pounds, they said.

29:46.040 --> 29:47.040
We haven't got any money.

29:47.040 --> 29:49.040
They know that.

29:49.040 --> 29:53.040
And our happy Christmas to you too, I shouted.

29:53.040 --> 29:57.040
Get out of here, said the policeman.

29:57.040 --> 29:58.040
We walked home.

29:58.040 --> 30:01.040
Me, Dad and Billy.

30:01.040 --> 30:04.040
I wanted to get home and go to bed.

30:04.040 --> 30:07.040
I wanted to cry like a little boy.

30:07.040 --> 30:10.040
But there was this woman in front of our house.

30:10.040 --> 30:12.040
Who's that?

30:12.040 --> 30:13.040
I asked.

30:13.040 --> 30:15.040
She came up to Billy.

30:15.040 --> 30:17.040
Did she know him?

30:17.040 --> 30:19.040
Where were you, Billy?

30:19.040 --> 30:21.040
What happened?

30:21.040 --> 30:25.040
Billy didn't want to say anything, but she waited.

30:25.040 --> 30:29.040
Our Tony was in court, he said quietly.

30:29.040 --> 30:30.040
I went too.

30:30.040 --> 30:33.040
He didn't look at her.

30:33.040 --> 30:36.040
Our Dad looked at Billy and this woman.

30:36.040 --> 30:39.040
Did he know her too?

30:39.040 --> 30:42.040
What's going on, I thought?

30:42.040 --> 30:44.040
Let's go in, Dad said.

30:44.040 --> 30:46.040
What's all this about, I said?

30:46.040 --> 30:48.040
I didn't want this.

30:48.040 --> 30:50.040
Things were bad enough.

30:50.040 --> 30:52.040
I didn't like this woman.

30:52.040 --> 30:53.040
She was posh.

30:53.040 --> 30:55.040
She had posh clothes.

30:55.040 --> 30:57.040
She wasn't like us.

30:57.040 --> 30:59.040
We went into the living room.

30:59.040 --> 31:01.040
Billy didn't look very happy.

31:01.040 --> 31:04.040
He's in trouble, I thought.

31:04.040 --> 31:06.040
Then she started.

31:06.040 --> 31:10.040
Today, Billy had an audition for the Royal Ballet School.

31:10.040 --> 31:13.040
I know things are difficult, but...

31:13.040 --> 31:15.040
I didn't believe my ears.

31:15.040 --> 31:16.040
I laughed.

31:16.040 --> 31:18.040
I looked at Billy and laughed again.

31:18.040 --> 31:19.040
What?

31:19.040 --> 31:21.040
Ballet, I said.

31:21.040 --> 31:25.040
I went over to the woman and shouted in her face.

31:25.040 --> 31:29.040
My brother does not do ballet, you stupid woman.

31:29.040 --> 31:33.040
My brother is not going to do ballet.

31:33.040 --> 31:35.040
Her face was white.

31:35.040 --> 31:38.040
She was frightened, but she didn't move.

31:38.040 --> 31:41.040
Don't shout at me, she said.

31:41.040 --> 31:43.040
Billy's a very good dancer.

31:43.040 --> 31:46.040
Where does he go after school every day?

31:46.040 --> 31:48.040
You don't know, and you don't care.

31:48.040 --> 31:50.040
I wanted to hit her.

31:50.040 --> 31:53.040
She knew, but she didn't care.

31:53.040 --> 31:55.040
Is Billy going to be like you?

31:55.040 --> 31:56.040
She said to me.

31:56.040 --> 31:58.040
No job, no hope.

31:58.040 --> 32:00.040
Do you want that for Billy?

32:00.040 --> 32:03.040
He's not going to be a scab, I shouted.

32:03.040 --> 32:05.040
Look at him.

32:05.040 --> 32:06.040
He's only twelve.

32:06.040 --> 32:07.040
He's a child.

32:07.040 --> 32:10.040
And you're putting stupid ideas in his head.

32:10.040 --> 32:13.040
You learn better when you're young, said Billy.

32:13.040 --> 32:15.040
Shut it, I shouted at him.

32:15.040 --> 32:16.040
I turned back to her.

32:16.040 --> 32:21.040
My brother is not running around in a stupid dress for you or anyone.

32:21.040 --> 32:23.040
It's not for me, she said.

32:23.040 --> 32:25.040
It's for Billy.

32:25.040 --> 32:26.040
And then she turned to Billy.

32:26.040 --> 32:29.040
See you Billy, she said, and walked out of the house.

32:29.040 --> 32:32.040
Get out of our house, I shouted at her.

32:32.040 --> 32:34.040
And don't come back.

32:34.040 --> 32:36.040
She didn't hear.

32:36.040 --> 32:38.040
I wanted to hit Billy then.

32:38.040 --> 32:40.040
I wanted to hit someone.

32:40.040 --> 32:42.040
But he was behind our dad.

32:42.040 --> 32:44.040
Shut up.

32:44.040 --> 32:45.040
I hate you.

32:45.040 --> 32:46.040
He shouted at me.

32:46.040 --> 32:47.040
I looked at him.

32:47.040 --> 32:49.040
He's right.

32:49.040 --> 32:51.040
He hates me, I thought.

32:51.040 --> 32:52.040
You little.

32:52.040 --> 32:54.040
I tried to hit him, but dad stopped me.

32:54.040 --> 32:57.040
Billy ran out of the back door.

32:57.040 --> 32:58.040
I looked at dad.

32:58.040 --> 33:01.040
I'm going to the pub, I said.

33:01.040 --> 33:03.040
I bang the door on my way out.

33:03.040 --> 33:06.040
And if I see that posh woman again.

33:09.040 --> 33:16.040
Chapter 9.

33:16.040 --> 33:19.040
Billy, you're in trouble now.

33:19.040 --> 33:24.040
That was the worst Christmas of my life, I said.

33:24.040 --> 33:26.040
I was with Michael.

33:26.040 --> 33:29.040
It was the day after Christmas, and we were out in the cold.

33:29.040 --> 33:31.040
No Christmas tree.

33:31.040 --> 33:33.040
No nothing.

33:33.040 --> 33:35.040
And no man.

33:35.040 --> 33:37.040
Have some of this.

33:37.040 --> 33:39.040
He had some of his dad's beer.

33:39.040 --> 33:40.040
I tried it.

33:40.040 --> 33:42.040
I don't like it.

33:42.040 --> 33:43.040
I said.

33:43.040 --> 33:45.040
What do you want to do then?

33:45.040 --> 33:46.040
That's Michael.

33:46.040 --> 33:48.040
Let's go to the social.

33:48.040 --> 33:49.040
Why?

33:49.040 --> 33:50.040
Michael asked.

33:50.040 --> 33:51.040
There's no one there now.

33:51.040 --> 33:53.040
So let's go.

33:53.040 --> 33:54.040
I said.

33:54.040 --> 33:55.040
And we went.

33:55.040 --> 33:59.040
Michael and I were in the boxing club.

33:59.040 --> 34:00.040
Okay.

34:00.040 --> 34:01.040
I said.

34:01.040 --> 34:03.040
You're the girl.

34:03.040 --> 34:06.040
Up and one and two.

34:06.040 --> 34:08.040
We did some of the moves together.

34:08.040 --> 34:10.040
It was good to dance again.

34:10.040 --> 34:12.040
Suddenly Michael stopped.

34:12.040 --> 34:13.040
What is it?

34:13.040 --> 34:15.040
I looked at the door.

34:15.040 --> 34:17.040
It was my dad.

34:17.040 --> 34:20.040
This time I didn't want to run.

34:20.040 --> 34:22.040
I didn't care.

34:22.040 --> 34:24.040
I walked over to him.

34:24.040 --> 34:26.040
I looked at him.

34:26.040 --> 34:29.040
And then I did my audition dance.

34:29.040 --> 34:31.040
I jumped and spun.

34:31.040 --> 34:34.040
I wanted to show dad everything.

34:34.040 --> 34:37.040
When I finished he didn't say anything.

34:37.040 --> 34:40.040
He looked at me and ran out of the room.

34:40.040 --> 34:42.040
Billy.

34:42.040 --> 34:44.040
What did you do that for?

34:44.040 --> 34:45.040
Said Michael.

34:45.040 --> 34:47.040
You're in big trouble now.

34:47.040 --> 34:49.040
He was right.

34:49.040 --> 34:53.040
But, well, that was Billy Elliot.

34:53.040 --> 34:55.040
Billy Elliot dances.

34:55.040 --> 34:57.040
That was me.

35:05.040 --> 35:07.040
Chapter 10.

35:07.040 --> 35:08.040
Jackie.

35:08.040 --> 35:10.040
The scab bus.

35:10.040 --> 35:13.040
I'm almost running down that road.

35:13.040 --> 35:14.040
Billy.

35:14.040 --> 35:16.040
Our Billy.

35:16.040 --> 35:18.040
He's good at something.

35:18.040 --> 35:19.040
No.

35:19.040 --> 35:20.040
Not good.

35:20.040 --> 35:21.040
Fantastic.

35:21.040 --> 35:24.040
Now, I don't know much about Bally.

35:24.040 --> 35:27.040
It's for posh people like that Mrs. Wilkinson.

35:27.040 --> 35:28.040
But maybe.

35:28.040 --> 35:30.040
Just maybe.

35:30.040 --> 35:32.040
My head spinning.

35:32.040 --> 35:35.040
And I'm thinking about my Sarah.

35:35.040 --> 35:36.040
My wife.

35:36.040 --> 35:39.040
I can almost hear her.

35:39.040 --> 35:41.040
Help the boy Jackie.

35:41.040 --> 35:42.040
What's wrong with you?

35:42.040 --> 35:44.040
He's our son.

35:44.040 --> 35:46.040
She's right.

35:46.040 --> 35:49.040
That Mrs. Wilkinson is right too.

35:49.040 --> 35:51.040
I'm going to see her.

35:51.040 --> 35:53.040
Now.

35:53.040 --> 35:56.040
Her husband opens the door.

35:56.040 --> 35:58.040
He looks at me.

35:58.040 --> 36:00.040
In there he says.

36:00.040 --> 36:02.040
I go into the living room.

36:02.040 --> 36:04.040
There she is with her cigarettes.

36:04.040 --> 36:07.040
How much has it gone to cost?

36:07.040 --> 36:08.040
I ask her.

36:08.040 --> 36:10.040
Happy Christmas to you too.

36:10.040 --> 36:11.040
She says.

36:11.040 --> 36:12.040
Then she smiles.

36:12.040 --> 36:14.040
Sit down.

36:14.040 --> 36:15.040
I'm okay.

36:15.040 --> 36:17.040
I don't want to stay for long.

36:17.040 --> 36:18.040
How much?

36:18.040 --> 36:20.040
For the audition.

36:20.040 --> 36:22.040
The cost of the bus to London.

36:22.040 --> 36:24.040
And a hotel for the night.

36:24.040 --> 36:26.040
I can help.

36:26.040 --> 36:28.040
I don't want your money.

36:28.040 --> 36:30.040
I say.

36:30.040 --> 36:32.040
How good is he?

36:32.040 --> 36:35.040
She smokes her cigarette and looks at me.

36:35.040 --> 36:38.040
He's the best Mr. Elliot.

36:38.040 --> 36:40.040
Thanks.

36:40.040 --> 36:41.040
I leave.

36:41.040 --> 36:43.040
I need time.

36:43.040 --> 36:45.040
I must think.

36:45.040 --> 36:47.040
What can I do?

36:47.040 --> 36:50.040
But I already know the answer.

36:50.040 --> 36:53.040
It's six o'clock in the morning.

36:53.040 --> 36:56.040
And I'm waiting for the bus with the other men.

36:56.040 --> 36:58.040
It's the scab bus.

36:58.040 --> 37:00.040
I'm doing it for Billy.

37:00.040 --> 37:02.040
I must help him.

37:02.040 --> 37:04.040
He's my son.

37:04.040 --> 37:06.040
I didn't sleep last night.

37:06.040 --> 37:08.040
I'm doing it for one week.

37:08.040 --> 37:12.040
One week's money for our Billy's audition.

37:12.040 --> 37:14.040
Our Tony doesn't know.

37:14.040 --> 37:16.040
No one knows yet.

37:16.040 --> 37:18.040
Only the other scabs.

37:18.040 --> 37:21.040
The bus comes and we all get on.

37:21.040 --> 37:24.040
No one speaks as we drive there.

37:24.040 --> 37:27.040
When we arrive, I can hear the men.

37:27.040 --> 37:30.040
Scab, scab, scab, they shout.

37:30.040 --> 37:32.040
I know the words.

37:32.040 --> 37:35.040
I shouted them last week.

37:35.040 --> 37:37.040
We drive through the men.

37:37.040 --> 37:39.040
Bang, bang, bang.

37:39.040 --> 37:41.040
They bang on the bus windows.

37:41.040 --> 37:43.040
The police try to stop them.

37:43.040 --> 37:45.040
The bus stops.

37:45.040 --> 37:48.040
Their faces are so close.

37:48.040 --> 37:50.040
I'm very frightened now.

37:50.040 --> 37:52.040
I look around me.

37:52.040 --> 37:55.040
Some of the scabs put their hands over their faces.

37:55.040 --> 37:56.040
Not me.

37:56.040 --> 37:58.040
I don't care.

37:58.040 --> 38:02.040
I look out of the window and then I see him.

38:02.040 --> 38:04.040
It's Tony.

38:04.040 --> 38:06.040
He's looking back at me.

38:06.040 --> 38:09.040
He can't believe his eyes.

38:09.040 --> 38:11.040
I don't know what to do.

38:11.040 --> 38:15.040
He can't believe his eyes.

38:15.040 --> 38:18.040
The bus moves on.

38:18.040 --> 38:20.040
Dad!

38:20.040 --> 38:22.040
Dad!

38:22.040 --> 38:24.040
What are you doing?

38:24.040 --> 38:26.040
I'm off the bus.

38:26.040 --> 38:28.040
I'm going to go into the mine.

38:28.040 --> 38:30.040
And there he is.

38:30.040 --> 38:32.040
Our Tony.

38:32.040 --> 38:34.040
He's calling to me.

38:34.040 --> 38:36.040
He's like a little boy again.

38:36.040 --> 38:38.040
I go over to him.

38:38.040 --> 38:40.040
I'm sorry, son.

38:40.040 --> 38:42.040
It's for Billy.

38:42.040 --> 38:43.040
I say.

38:43.040 --> 38:45.040
And then I start to cry.

38:45.040 --> 38:47.040
You can't go back, Dad.

38:47.040 --> 38:49.040
Not now.

38:49.040 --> 38:51.040
Tony looks at me.

38:51.040 --> 38:53.040
And he's crying too.

38:53.040 --> 38:55.040
There's another way, Dad.

38:55.040 --> 38:57.040
We can help Billy.

38:57.040 --> 38:59.040
Please.

39:01.040 --> 39:03.040
So I didn't go into the mine.

39:03.040 --> 39:05.040
I went home without Tony.

39:05.040 --> 39:08.040
I told him all about Billy in the ballet.

39:08.040 --> 39:11.040
We're going to find that money, Dad, he said.

39:11.040 --> 39:13.040
Billy's going to the audition.

39:13.040 --> 39:16.040
Tony had to be strong.

39:16.040 --> 39:18.040
I wasn't.

39:18.040 --> 39:20.040
Not now.

39:28.040 --> 39:30.040
Chapter 11.

39:30.040 --> 39:31.040
Billy.

39:31.040 --> 39:33.040
A stupid dream.

39:33.040 --> 39:37.040
I'm on a bus to London with me, Dad.

39:37.040 --> 39:39.040
I can't believe it.

39:39.040 --> 39:42.040
Wasn't it all a stupid dream?

39:42.040 --> 39:45.040
Me and the Royal Ballet School.

39:45.040 --> 39:48.040
But people in the town helped with the money.

39:48.040 --> 39:50.040
We had a dance at the social.

39:50.040 --> 39:54.040
And then there were some of my mom's things.

39:54.040 --> 39:58.040
I'm going to sell them, Dad said one morning.

39:58.040 --> 40:01.040
I don't want to think about that.

40:01.040 --> 40:05.040
I hated the Royal Ballet School when I saw it.

40:05.040 --> 40:08.040
It was so big and posh.

40:08.040 --> 40:11.040
How much is this going to cost, Dad said?

40:11.040 --> 40:14.040
I changed into my dance clothes.

40:14.040 --> 40:16.040
There were other boys there.

40:16.040 --> 40:18.040
They were posh too.

40:18.040 --> 40:20.040
They didn't understand my English.

40:20.040 --> 40:23.040
Sorry, what did you say?

40:23.040 --> 40:25.040
Oh, shut it.

40:25.040 --> 40:27.040
Then there was the audition.

40:27.040 --> 40:31.040
There were five people from the Royal Ballet School there.

40:31.040 --> 40:33.040
They sat behind a long table.

40:33.040 --> 40:35.040
They didn't like me.

40:35.040 --> 40:37.040
Do you have some music, Billy?

40:37.040 --> 40:39.040
I gave it to them.

40:39.040 --> 40:41.040
T-Rex.

40:41.040 --> 40:43.040
It wasn't right for that place.

40:43.040 --> 40:45.040
All that now.

40:45.040 --> 40:46.040
I didn't dance.

40:46.040 --> 40:48.040
I didn't move.

40:48.040 --> 40:50.040
I just looked at them.

40:50.040 --> 40:53.040
Then I heard Miss in my ear.

40:53.040 --> 40:56.040
Billy, you're not trying.

40:56.040 --> 40:57.040
Go on.

40:57.040 --> 40:59.040
Just do it.

40:59.040 --> 41:01.040
So I did it.

41:01.040 --> 41:03.040
Badly.

41:03.040 --> 41:06.040
When I finished, nobody said anything.

41:06.040 --> 41:09.040
They wrote some things down.

41:09.040 --> 41:11.040
Then one of them said,

41:11.040 --> 41:13.040
Thank you, Billy.

41:13.040 --> 41:15.040
You can go now.

41:15.040 --> 41:17.040
I almost ran out of there.

41:17.040 --> 41:19.040
All that work.

41:19.040 --> 41:20.040
All that money.

41:20.040 --> 41:21.040
For nothing.

41:21.040 --> 41:24.040
I just wanted to go home.

41:24.040 --> 41:27.040
But it wasn't over.

41:27.040 --> 41:30.040
They called me and Dad into the audition room again.

41:30.040 --> 41:33.040
We sat in front of that long table.

41:33.040 --> 41:36.040
Now, Billy, we have some questions for you.

41:36.040 --> 41:38.040
One of them said,

41:38.040 --> 41:40.040
Why do you like ballet?

41:40.040 --> 41:41.040
I didn't answer.

41:41.040 --> 41:43.040
I wasn't right for this place.

41:43.040 --> 41:45.040
Don't know, I said.

41:45.040 --> 41:48.040
Well, what do you like about dancing?

41:48.040 --> 41:50.040
Dad looked at me.

41:50.040 --> 41:53.040
Um, everything.

41:53.040 --> 41:56.040
He dances all the time, my Dad said.

41:56.040 --> 42:00.040
Yes, we've got a letter from Mrs Wilkinson here.

42:00.040 --> 42:01.040
I knew Mr Elliot.

42:01.040 --> 42:03.040
Did you like ballet?

42:03.040 --> 42:07.040
Um, well, I don't know much about it, Dad said.

42:07.040 --> 42:09.040
Well, that was true.

42:09.040 --> 42:11.040
And that was about it.

42:11.040 --> 42:13.040
We got up and walked to the door.

42:13.040 --> 42:15.040
One more thing, Billy.

42:15.040 --> 42:18.040
Said a very posh woman.

42:18.040 --> 42:22.040
How do you feel when you dance?

42:22.040 --> 42:24.040
I thought for a minute.

42:24.040 --> 42:26.040
I feel good.

42:26.040 --> 42:28.040
I started.

42:28.040 --> 42:31.040
When I dance, I forget the world.

42:31.040 --> 42:33.040
And the strike.

42:33.040 --> 42:35.040
And everything.

42:35.040 --> 42:38.040
There's fire in my body.

42:38.040 --> 42:40.040
It's like...

42:40.040 --> 42:43.040
It's like flying.

42:43.040 --> 42:46.040
That sounded stupid, I thought.

42:55.040 --> 42:56.040
Chapter 12.

42:56.040 --> 42:58.040
Jackie.

42:58.040 --> 43:00.040
The letter.

43:00.040 --> 43:02.040
Poor Billy.

43:02.040 --> 43:05.040
When we got home, he went to bed.

43:05.040 --> 43:07.040
He didn't want any dinner.

43:07.040 --> 43:09.040
He didn't want to talk.

43:09.040 --> 43:11.040
And that place.

43:11.040 --> 43:14.040
It was a different world.

43:14.040 --> 43:16.040
All those rich boys.

43:16.040 --> 43:18.040
Special dancing lessons.

43:18.040 --> 43:19.040
Big houses.

43:19.040 --> 43:21.040
Posh cars.

43:21.040 --> 43:23.040
It wasn't off.

43:23.040 --> 43:27.040
But the royal ballet people.

43:27.040 --> 43:30.040
Maybe they weren't so bad.

43:30.040 --> 43:34.040
When we left the audition room, one of the teachers said,

43:34.040 --> 43:38.040
Good luck with the strike, Mr. Elliot.

43:38.040 --> 43:40.040
We waited one week.

43:40.040 --> 43:42.040
Two weeks.

43:42.040 --> 43:45.040
Then the letter arrived.

43:45.040 --> 43:47.040
Billy was at school.

43:47.040 --> 43:49.040
It was a long day.

43:49.040 --> 43:51.040
Billy came home at four o'clock.

43:51.040 --> 43:54.040
We were all there.

43:54.040 --> 43:57.040
Billy took the letter.

43:57.040 --> 43:59.040
No one said anything.

43:59.040 --> 44:03.040
He went into his nuns' room and closed the door.

44:03.040 --> 44:05.040
Then.

44:05.040 --> 44:07.040
Nothing.

44:07.040 --> 44:09.040
He didn't come out.

44:09.040 --> 44:12.040
In the end, we went in there.

44:12.040 --> 44:14.040
I opened the door.

44:14.040 --> 44:18.040
Billy started to cry.

44:18.040 --> 44:19.040
I did it.

44:19.040 --> 44:21.040
He said quietly.

44:21.040 --> 44:23.040
I'm in.

44:25.040 --> 44:27.040
Yes!

44:27.040 --> 44:29.040
I ran up the road to the social.

44:29.040 --> 44:30.040
He did it.

44:30.040 --> 44:32.040
Our Billy.

44:32.040 --> 44:34.040
I wanted to tell everyone.

44:34.040 --> 44:36.040
I ran into the social.

44:36.040 --> 44:37.040
He's in.

44:37.040 --> 44:38.040
He did it.

44:38.040 --> 44:40.040
Nobody answered.

44:40.040 --> 44:42.040
It's over, Jackie.

44:42.040 --> 44:44.040
We're going back.

44:44.040 --> 44:46.040
What?

44:46.040 --> 44:48.040
The strike's over.

44:48.040 --> 44:52.040
We're going back to work on Monday.

44:52.040 --> 44:54.040
So that was it.

44:54.040 --> 44:58.040
The mind didn't stay open very long after that.

44:58.040 --> 45:00.040
That was ten years ago now.

45:00.040 --> 45:03.040
It was the end for me.

45:03.040 --> 45:07.040
But life is only just starting for Billy.

45:07.040 --> 45:09.040
And that's something.

45:17.040 --> 45:19.040
Epilogue.

45:19.040 --> 45:20.040
Jackie.

45:20.040 --> 45:22.040
Our Billy.

45:22.040 --> 45:25.040
Well, London doesn't change.

45:25.040 --> 45:27.040
It's still big.

45:27.040 --> 45:29.040
It's still expensive.

45:29.040 --> 45:31.040
But we didn't pay for our ballet tickets.

45:31.040 --> 45:33.040
I'm sitting here without Tony.

45:33.040 --> 45:37.040
It's funny to see your name in big letters.

45:37.040 --> 45:38.040
There.

45:38.040 --> 45:41.040
On the front of the Royal Opera House.

45:41.040 --> 45:43.040
The Royal Ballet.

45:43.040 --> 45:45.040
Billy Elliot.

45:45.040 --> 45:47.040
Our Billy.

45:47.040 --> 45:50.040
Then the music starts.

45:50.040 --> 45:52.040
And there he is.

45:52.040 --> 45:55.040
He runs on and jumps.

45:55.040 --> 45:56.040
What a jump!

45:56.040 --> 45:58.040
No one does it like Billy.

45:58.040 --> 46:00.040
He spins and spins.

46:00.040 --> 46:02.040
Everyone's watching.

46:02.040 --> 46:04.040
He's the best.

46:04.040 --> 46:05.040
And he's smiling all the time.

46:05.040 --> 46:07.040
He's smiling at us.

46:07.040 --> 46:09.040
So I stand up and I shout,

46:09.040 --> 46:11.040
Billy, Billy Elliot.

46:11.040 --> 46:13.040
Tony's standing with me.

46:13.040 --> 46:15.040
Our Billy, his shouts.

46:15.040 --> 46:17.040
And other people stand up too.

46:17.040 --> 46:19.040
And you know,

46:19.040 --> 46:21.040
I'm never going to forget this.

